  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Chat is the format you type most - so let's make it automatic. Same word on repeat until your fingers fire it without thinking. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on home row, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word at one even pace - same gap between every tap. Don't rush the reply, just keep the beat steady."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🎶",
      "title": "Even beat",
      "text": "Set a tempo you can hold and stay in it. Smooth and even beats fast and jerky every time - in chat, steady hands answer quicker than panicked ones. Let the rhythm lead."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "cool cool cool cool cool",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: cool",
      "hint": "Loop it on the beat: cool - cool - cool. Same gap every time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "snacks snacks snacks snacks",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: snacks",
      "hint": "Hold the tempo: snacks - snacks - snacks. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "safe safe safe safe",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: safe",
      "hint": "Stay even to the end: safe - safe - safe. Don't rush the finish."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Feel your fingers grabbing the whole word at once? That is exactly it - even reps turn thinking into reflex, and reflex is what lets you fire off a reply without looking down."
    },
